svg.text: The Rings and Satellites of Jupiter
Galileo Galilei discovers Jupiter's four largest moons
Pioneer 10 is the first spacecraft to visit Jupiter
Voyagers 1 and 2 arrive at Jupiter, ring system is discovered
Ulysses probe passes Jupiter, using its gravity to enter polar orbit around the Sun
Galileo orbiter arrives at Jupiter and remains in the Jovian system until 2003
Cassini probe passes Jupiter en route to Saturn
Galileo missions ends, orbiter descends into Jupiter's atmosphere
New Horizons probe passes Jupiter en route to Pluto
Juno probe enters polar orbit around Jupiter
